# Frontend: service class → hooks → axios

```
Component / Page
      ↓
<domain>.hooks.ts          ← React Query wrappers only
      ↓
<domain>.service.ts        ← class, one method per endpoint
      ↓
api.ts                     ← shared axios instance (origin only)
```

## Responsibilities

1. **`<domain>.hooks.ts`** — thin `useQuery` / `useMutation` wrappers. Owns
   `queryKey`, `staleTime`, `enabled`. No fetch/axios calls.

2. **`<domain>.service.ts`** — a **class** with a `private static readonly
   BASE_PATH` (e.g. `"/api/infloww"`). Exports a singleton instance. Knows
   nothing about React.

3. **`api.ts`** — one axios instance. `baseURL` is the **origin only**
   (`window.location.origin` / `http://localhost:3000`). Each service class
   prepends `BASE_PATH`. Owns the error interceptor (`ApiError`).

## URL composition

```
axios baseURL              service BASE_PATH     endpoint
http://localhost:3000   +  /api/infloww       +  /creators
```

## File naming

All domain files follow the `<domain>.<layer>.ts` pattern:
`infloww.hooks.ts`, `infloww.service.ts`.

## Location

Colocate `<domain>.hooks.ts`, `<domain>.service.ts`, `api.ts`, and
domain-specific types/utils under `src/lib/<domain>/`.

Shared helpers (derive functions, date range utils, formatters) go in
`src/lib/utils/`.
